So as Hannah Montana...

232
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:49,354
...Miley was a world-famous pop star.

233
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:52,273
She would take off her wig
and go to school like a normal girl.

234
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:56,109
Which, I don't have to tell you,
at that age, is its own headache.

235
00:13:57,360 --> 00:14:01,433
That's preposterous. How would she go
unrecognized just by wearing a wig?

236
00:14:01,639 --> 00:14:04,711
But you're okay with Superman
concealing his identity with glasses?

237
00:14:04,879 --> 00:14:06,756
He doesn'tjust put on a pair of glasses.

238
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:10,953
He combs back his curlicue
and affects a mild-mannered personality.

239
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:13,718
AMY:
You guys doing okay down there?

240
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:16,229
I told you to use the walkie-talkie.

241
00:14:17,959 --> 00:14:20,348
AMY [OVER RADIO]:
You guys doing okay down there?

242
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:24,950
Please keep this channel clear
for emergencies. Thank you.

243
00:14:25,959 --> 00:14:28,473
I'm going to the vending machine.
Do you want anything?

244
00:14:29,199 --> 00:14:32,555
This is a simulation. We have to survive
on the supplies we brought.

245
00:14:32,719 --> 00:14:34,994
Okay. Just checking.

246
00:14:35,199 --> 00:14:37,554
We should have asked her
to get some Funyuns.

247
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:41,711
You're not going to have Funyuns
when we're a mile below the Earth.

248
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:43,956
What if we brought them down with us?

249
00:14:45,079 --> 00:14:46,797
We'll take some Funyuns.

250
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:49,392
Anything else?

251
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:52,398
Some York Peppermint Patties,
a couple of Dr Peppers...

252
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:55,672
...and run to Best Buy and see if
they have a portable DVD player...

253
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:58,952
...and season one of a show
called Hannah Montana.

254
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:03,879
Have her get season two.
Season one it was still finding itself.

255
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:07,430
Sorry you guys had to see that.

256
00:15:07,639 --> 00:15:09,789
-Don't apologize.
-It makes it harder...

257
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,991
...to pretend it never happened.

258
00:15:12,399 --> 00:15:15,835
Money's a sensitive subject for Howie
because of the difference in our income.

259
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:17,075
It really bothers him?

260
00:15:17,279 --> 00:15:20,077
Sure. There's still a lot of pressure
on guys to be providers.

261
00:15:20,279 --> 00:15:23,191
So even though he's happy for me,
it's just a little tough on him.

262
00:15:23,360 --> 00:15:24,349
Uh-oh.

263
00:15:24,519 --> 00:15:25,952
-What?
-We||...

264
00:15:26,159 --> 00:15:28,878
...ifl do well in sales, I could end up
making more than you.

265
00:15:29,079 --> 00:15:31,035
Not a problem. I grew up with a mother...

266
00:15:31,199 --> 00:15:35,238
...who emasculated my father financially
and in every other aspect of his life.

267
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:38,793
Really, it's what I think love looks like.

268
00:15:40,879 --> 00:15:43,109
I'll be right back.
I'm gonna go check on him.

269
00:15:45,040 --> 00:15:48,555
Maybe it's a good thing we came here.
It's like a lesson in what not to do.

270
00:15:48,759 --> 00:15:50,909
I don't want money to come between us.

271
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:54,396
It won't. Let's promise to figure
this stuff out before we get married.

272
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:58,235
HOWARD: Why are you being so bossy?
BERNADETTE: Why are you being a baby?

273
00:15:58,480 --> 00:16:04,112
HOWARD: I'm not a baby. I'm a grown man,
and I made the bed. Now where's my star?

274
00:16:06,839 --> 00:16:10,718
-Should we go?
-Hang on. I wanna see if he gets the star.

275
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,831
This heat is brutal.

276
00:16:16,039 --> 00:16:18,428
As someone from the
tropical subcontinent of India...

277
00:16:18,639 --> 00:16:21,028
...you should know fanning yourself
in a humid environment...

278
00:16:21,199 --> 00:16:23,030
...raises your body temperature.

279
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:25,794
Huh. That does explain why the servants
used to look so hot...

280
00:16:25,959 --> 00:16:27,597
...while they were fanning me.

281
00:16:28,879 --> 00:16:31,154
Let's get our minds off
how uncomfortable we are.

282
00:16:31,360 --> 00:16:33,794
We could take some more
simulated instrument readings.

283
00:16:33,999 --> 00:16:37,230
My major focus at the moment
is keeping my claustrophobia at bay.

284
00:16:37,439 --> 00:16:39,430
-How's that going?
-You tell me.

285
00:16:39,639 --> 00:16:43,109
I feel like I can't breathe,
and I am tempted to crack you open...

286
00:16:43,319 --> 00:16:45,753
...and suck the air right out of your lungs.

287
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:49,430
Sheldon, if this is too much, we can stop.

288
00:16:49,639 --> 00:16:52,153
-We're not stopping.
-You don't have to bite my head off.

289
00:16:52,639 --> 00:16:55,153
I apologize. ljust--

290
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:57,828
I'm plagued by an internal struggle.

291
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:01,749
If you would just use the bucket,
you'd be so much more comfortable.

292
00:17:02,920 --> 00:17:04,751
My struggle is emotional.

293
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:08,552
-Is it Amy?
-lt's dark matter.

294
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:13,349
When I entered the field of string theory,
I was a prodigy.

295
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:16,910
l rose to a position of respect...

296
00:17:17,120 --> 00:17:21,159
...and I assumed my career would
continue on that upward trajectory.

297
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:24,236
Now here I am in my 30s.

298
00:17:24,439 --> 00:17:26,828
I'm back at square one.

299
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,991
And frankly, it's frightening.

300
00:17:31,799 --> 00:17:34,472
Sheldon, you know what
I think of when I'm scared?

301
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:36,471
Voyager.

302
00:17:37,039 --> 00:17:41,430
Voyager the space probe,
or Voyager the Star Trek TV show?

303
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,877
-The space probe.
-Good.

304
00:17:44,080 --> 00:17:47,436
I am too hot and tired to go on about
how much I hate Voyagerthe TV show.

305
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:52,989
By the time I was born, Voyager 1's
mission was supposed to be over.

306
00:17:53,199 --> 00:17:56,828
It had seen Jupiter
and Saturn and all their moons...

307
00:17:57,039 --> 00:17:58,950
...but it kept going.

308
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:04,393
When I left India for America,
I was never more scared in my life.

309
00:18:04,759 --> 00:18:06,670
I had no idea what lay ahead.

310
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:11,274
Whenever I feel that way,
I think about how Voyager is...

311
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:13,152
...still out there.

312
00:18:13,360 --> 00:18:15,476
Somewhere beyond our solar system.

313
00:18:15,679 --> 00:18:18,147
Going further than anyone
ever thought it could.

314
00:18:21,839 --> 00:18:23,955
Don't leave. You can do this.

315
00:18:26,559 --> 00:18:27,787
Sheldon, is everything okay?

316
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:30,150
It's too late for Koothrappali. Let's go.

317
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:36,194
Eleven minutes.
That's longer than I thought.

318
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:40,558
RAJ: They're in my shirt.
They're in my shirt. They're in my shirt!

319
00:18:45,439 --> 00:18:48,476
Okay, this is definitely the most fun thing
we can do with the money.

320
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:55,114
I've never done it on
a big old pile of cash before.

321
00:18:58,640 --> 00:19:01,438
"Me neither, Leonard.
It's my first time too."

322
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:08,234
I'm so sorry I made you
feel bad about the money stuff.

323
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:11,034
-lt's okay.
-No. It's not okay.

324
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:13,549
I want us to be partners. Equals.

325
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:15,955
Adults in a mature relationship.

326
00:19:16,159 --> 00:19:18,229
I want that too.

327
00:19:19,479 --> 00:19:21,390
Now, let's talk about your birthday party.

328
00:19:21,599 --> 00:19:23,590
Ooh, Laser tag. Laser tag.

329
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:29,510
-Do you really need me to transcribe this?
-You're not doing it for me.

330
00:19:29,720 --> 00:19:33,554
You're doing it for future generations
who will benefit from my struggle.

331
00:19:35,079 --> 00:19:37,309
SHELDON [ON RECORDING]:
Sheldon 's mine simulation log.

332
00:19:38,479 --> 00:19:39,992
Entry four.

333
00:19:40,199 --> 00:19:42,554
My Kit Kat has melted.

334
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:46,116
All is lost.

335
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:49,152
You call yourself a friend?

336
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:52,911
l was trying to help you,
and at the first sign of trouble...

337
00:19:53,119 --> 00:19:57,510
...you ran away,
leaving me to fend off a family of rats.

338
00:19:58,359 --> 00:20:03,194
You're a completely selfish human being
and a physical and moral coward.

339
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:07,708
His statements of the obvious
continue to annoy.

340
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,391
